K-Armed Bandit Game

Assume that you have k one armed bandit machines (A game machine that is popular in Las Vegas)

Machine M1 returns a reward that is normal distributed with a mean of μ_1= and a standard deviation of σ_1 =

Machine M2 returns a reward that is normal distributed with a mean of μ_2= and a standard deviation of σ_2 =

You do not know the underlying distributions

You have enough time to play N= games

What is the goal?

  • Maximize the reward over N= games

How would you play?

  • The strategy you play is called the policy π (pi)
import random

def createBandits( kBandits ):
  bandits = []

  for i in range( kBandits ):
    mu = random.gauss( 0, 2 )
    sigma = -1
    while (sigma <= 0):
      sigma = random.gauss( 1, 1 )
    bandits.append( [mu, sigma ])
  return bandits
